headline.main: 2 NAMED WINNERS OF HARMON PRIZES; Max Conrad and Late Mrs. Smith Hailed for Flights

results.snippet: Max Conrad, who is known as the flying grandfather, and the late Mrs. Joan Merriam Smith, who flew around the world to accomplish what Amelia Earhart had been trying to do in 1937 when she disappeared, were named yesterday as this year's winners of...
results.lead_paragraph: Max Conrad, who is known as the flying grandfather, and the late Mrs. Joan Merriam Smith, who flew around the world to accomplish what Amelia Earhart had been trying to do in 1937 when she disappeared, were named yesterday as this year's winners of the Harmon International Aviation Trophies.
